title: For Sale:  Bulletproof Vest - Better than IIIA - Resistant To Stab Attacks
postcontent: I would like to sell my bulletproof vest, which is also known as body armor.  This bulletproof vest is from the "soft armor" category of bulletproof vests. This means that it is designed to be concealed underneath clothing and give protection mostly from handgun ammunition.  This bulletproof vest is from Germany and is a police surplus item. The maker of this bulletproof vest (Mehler) is the largest and most advanced body armor manufacturer in Europe. The protection ratings on this vest are rated in Germany as SK-1 and ST1. (The German standard of SK-1 surpasses the NIJ rating of IIIA, which is the highest NIJ rating for soft body armor.)   The German standard of SK-1 is the highest level of ballistic protection for soft body armor vests. The German standard of ST1 is the highest level of stab protection for soft body armor vests. The wearer of this vest will gain protection from both shots fired (from handgun rounds, but not rifle rounds) as well as stab injuries from knives and other sharp objects, such as ice picks, sharpened screwdrivers, etc.   The national police in Germany have had a long-time reputation around the entire world for maintaining the highest standards for bulletproof vests. The German SK rating system goes beyond the NIJ "Level" system. The German SK rating system is more demanding for performance than any other law enforcement standard.  This bulletproof vest fits very well on men who wear a size large or size extra large t-shirt. I wear a Size 42 jacket, and this vest fit on me very well when I tried it on just once for size.  This bulletproof vest is fully concealable under many types of shirts and jackets. The carrier on this bulletproof vest is khaki-colored on the exterior and khaki-colored on the interior.
